Important information

1. About This Site
This website and the material contained in it, is aimed only at
UK occupational pension scheme trustees, consultants and UK
resident scheme members whose employers have chosen us to manage
their investments. This website is not directed at persons in any
other jurisdiction. Specifically it is not aimed at US persons.
Threadneedle Asset Management Limited or
associated companies do not give investment advice or
recommendations in respect of its product range and nothing in this
website should be taken as an offer to buy or sell investments,
products or funds. Investment decisions should not be made solely
on the basis of information provided in this site. If you are in
any doubt about the suitability of any investment you should speak
to your financial adviser.
Any research or analysis included in the website has been
produced by Threadneedle Asset Management Limited or associated
companies for its own investment management activities, may have
been acted upon prior to publication of this note and is made
available here incidentally. In some instances the information
contained in this note, other than statements of fact, was obtained
from external sources believed to be reliable but its accuracy of
completeness cannot be guaranteed. Any opinions, expressed are made
in good faith, but are subject to change without notice. Although
we shall use all reasonable endeavours to ensure that the
information on our website is kept up-to-date, we cannot be held
responsible for any losses or damage incurred as a result of using
any out-of-date or superseded documentation on this website.
No other UK based person/company (including other financial
services sector related companies) may link their website into our
website (www.threadneedlepensions.co.uk) without the express
written permission of us. As this site is aimed at UK investors
only, no non-UK (and specifically US) persons/companies may link or
make reference to this site.
2. Important Performance Information
Past performance is not a guide to the future. The value of
investments, and the income from them, can go down as well as up.
You may not get back the amount you have invested. You should be
aware that currency fluctuations may also affect the value of an
investment. Prices and performance details are for information
purposes only.
3. Taxation
Tax concessions are not guaranteed, depend on your own
circumstances and may change in the future. Tax-free means the
investor pays no tax. Threadneedle Asset Management
Limited and associate companies do not provide taxation
advice. If you have any doubts you should seek professional
advice.
4. Data Protection
For the purposes of the Data Protection Act 1998, the data
controller in relation to any personal data you supply is
Threadneedle Pensions Limited. Sometimes your details may be made
available to external servicing companies, for the purpose of
administering your account and communicating with you. With limited
exceptions you have a right of access to the data that we hold
about you. You agree that we may use, disclose and transfer
personal data as described in this statement.
On occasions we may want to send you marketing material relating
to our products. Sometimes your details may be made available to
external marketing companies for marketing purposes. If you do not
wish to receive such marketing approaches, please write to
Threadneedle Pensions Limited, Cannon Place, 78 Cannon Street,
London EC4N 6AG.
5. About Threadneedle Investments
Threadneedle Pensions Limited. Registered in England and Wales,
No. 984167. Registered Office: Cannon Place, 78 Cannon Street,
London, EC4N 6AG. Authorised by the Prudential Regulation Authority
and regulated by the Financial Conduct Authority and the Prudential
Regulation Authority. Threadneedle Asset Management Limited is the
investment manager to the Threadneedle Pooled Pension Fund range
and is authorised and regulated by the Financial Conduct
Authority.
The VAT number for all Threadneedle Investments group companies
is 107831677.
Issued by Threadneedle Pensions Limited
"Columbia Threadneedle Investments" is a brand owned by
Threadneedle's ultimate parent company, Ameriprise Financial, Inc.,
and is the subject of international applications for service mark
registration. No permission or licence is granted to use this brand
or any registered mark that results from such applications without
the prior written consent of Ameriprise Financial, Inc. All other
intellectual and other property and rights therein on this website
remain property of the Threadneedle group of companies and no
rights of any kind to any such property will pass to users of this
website.













© 2017 THREADNEEDLE ASSET MANAGEMENT HOLDINGS LIMITED 
				Issued by Threadneedle Pensions Limited. Authorised and Regulated in the UK by the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA). Columbia Threadneedle Investments is the global brand name of the Columbia and Threadneedle group of companies.
			






